<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Miley Cyrus performed a soulful rendition of Hall &amp; Oates' hit 1982 track, Maneater, after ending her nearly year-long romance with Cody Simpson in August. </p>

<p>During her virtual appearance on Thursday evening's The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon, the self-proclaimed 'freshly single' singer spoke about the song choice. </p>

<p>When the 45-year-old late-night host asked what prompted her cover, the 27-year-old Grammy nominee explained she felt it was 'very important to be transparent.' </p>

<p>Cheeky choice: Miley Cyrus performed a soulful rendition of Hall &amp; Oates' hit 1982 track, Maneater, after ending her nearly year-long romance with Cody Simpson in August </p>

<p>'I'm freshly single, so anyone watching that's my future ex-husband, just know, I told you,' she joked, after singing about being a seductive woman who uses men.</p>

<p>After 14 years in the public eye, she teased about not having any 'skeletons' in her closet and that her performance was a warning to her next partner. </p>

<p>Cyrus recently split from Simpson, whom she began dating after the end of her marriage to Liam Hemsworth and a short-lived romance with Kaitlynn Carter. </p>

